The paper deals with the prediction of supply and demand for autonomous vehicles using intelligent transportation systems. This involves the use of machine learning techniques such as residual networks, LSTM, and attention mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with artificial intelligence and machine learning. The paper also involves the use of computer vision techniques for spatial dependency, which falls under cs.CV. The prediction models are used for control, which falls under cs.RO (robotics). Finally, the paper involves the use of autocorrelation coefficient method, which falls under cs.IT (information theory).
